{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior"],"title":"Related Documentation","anchor":"Related-Documentation"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference"],"title":"Reference","anchor":"Reference"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The UI product layers two "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" types and a convenience modifier on top of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI"},{"type":"text","text":". Each is a stateless wrapper bound to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"type":"text","text":": presentation flags drive visibility, and dismissal closures dispatch matching paywall actions back through the store."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For step-by-step wiring, see "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Present the UI"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" documentation. For the rationale behind platform-specific behavior, see "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform Behavior"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" in the same catalog."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Library target","anchor":"Library-target"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Product: ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Import: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The UI product depends on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI"},{"type":"text","text":", both pulled in transitively. Apps that don’t ship paywall UI in the same target (for example, a tests-only target) can depend on the lower-level "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" product alone."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Types","anchor":"Types"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"PaywallSheet","text":"`PaywallSheet`"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public struct PaywallSheet: View {","    public init(isPresented: Bool, onDismiss: @escaping () -> Void)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Wraps ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}]},{"text":" — Presents in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"text":" so the paywall takes the full screen.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]},{"text":" — Presents in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"text":" sized to a 400×600 minimum.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Place anywhere in the view tree; the body is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EmptyView"},{"type":"text","text":" plus the platform-appropriate presentation modifier, so attaching via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".background"},{"type":"text","text":" keeps it out of layout."}]},{"level":4,"type":"heading","anchor":"Initializer","text":"Initializer"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" — Whether the sheet is visible. Pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"store.paywall.isPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. The plugin owns this flag."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"text":" — Called when the user dismisses the sheet. Dispatch ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall(.dismiss)"},{"text":" so the plugin clears its presentation state and triggers an entitlement refresh.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"`CustomerCenterSheet`","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"CustomerCenterSheet"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public struct CustomerCenterSheet: View {","    public init(isPresented: Bool, onDismiss: @escaping () -> Void)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Adapts to platform support for RevenueCat’s customer center."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Presents "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Opens "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"itms-apps:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions"},{"type":"text","text":" via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSWorkspace.shared.open"},{"type":"text","text":" and immediately fires "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"type":"text","text":". RevenueCatUI